Detailed Description

Packages all of the Mutation++ functionality pertaining to a mixture into a single class.

A Mixture object simply inherits all functionalities from the Thermodynamics, Transport, and Kinetics classes. A Mixture object can be constructed using a mixture file name or a MixtureOptions object.

See also
Thermodynamics::Thermodynamics
Transport::Transport
Kinetics::Kinetics

◆ equilDiffFluxFacsP()

void equilDiffFluxFacsP ( double *const  p_F)
inherited

Computes the vector of elemental mass and energy diffusion fluxes per pressure gradient for a mixture in equilibrium, \(\mathcal{F}_k^p\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^p\), where.

\[ \mathcal{F}_k^p = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i \frac{M_{w,k}}{M_{w,i}} \nu_i^k \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \left( \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial p} + \frac{x_j - y_j}{p} \right), \quad \forall\;k\in\mathcal{E}, \]

and

\[ \mathcal{F}_h^p = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \left( \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial p} + \frac{x_j - y_j}{p} \right). \]

The total mass diffusion flux of element \(k\) for a mixture at equilibrium can then be computed with

\[ \rho_k V_k = \mathcal{F}_k^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_k^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_k^{z_l} \nabla z_l, \quad \forall\;k\in\mathcal{E}. \]

The total energy diffusion flux is computed by

\[ \sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i V_i = \mathcal{F}_h^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_h^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_h^{z_l} \nabla z_l. \]

Parameters
p_F- A vector with length greater than the number of elements plus one. On return, the vector will correspond to \(\{\mathcal{F}^p_1, \cdots, \mathcal{F}^p_{N_e}, \mathcal{F}^p_h\}\).
See also
equilDiffFluxFacsT for \(\mathcal{F}_k^T\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^T\)
equilDiffFluxFacsZ for \(\mathcal{F}_k^{z_l}\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^{z_l}\)

Solves a surface mass balance (SMB) equation for a pure Carbon char and returns the non-dimensional ablation mass flux and wall enthalpy.

The elemental SMB is given for each element \(k\) as

\[ y_{w,k}(B'_c + B'_g + 1) = B'_c y_{c,k} + B'_g y_{g,k} + y_{e,k}, \]

where \(B'\) is a non-dimenaional mass flux, defined as \(\dot{m}/ (\rho_e u_e C_M)\). Subscripts \(c, g, w\) refer to char, pyrolysis gas, and wall quantities, respectively and \(y_{z,k}\) is the elemenal mass fraction of element \(k\) for gas \(z\). In this implementation, it is assumed that \(y_{c,C} = 1\) (pure carbon char).

Parameters
p_YkeElement mass fractions of boundary layer edge.
p_YkgElement mass fractions of the pyrolysis gas.
TTemperature at the surface in K.
PPressure at the surface in Pa.
BgNon-dimensional pyrolysis gas mass blowing rate.
BcOn return, non-dimensional char gas mass blowing rate.
hwOn return, enthalpy of the mixed gas at the surface in J/kg.
p_Xs(optional) On return, vector of species mole fractions at the surface.
